==English==

===Pronunciation===
*lŭkʹē, {{IPA|/ˈlʌki/}}, {{SAMPA|/"lVki/}}

===Etymology===
[[luck]] + [[-y]]

===Adjective===
{{en-ad2|'''[[lucky]]'''|'''[[luckier]]'''|'''[[luckiest]]'''}}

#[[Favor]]ed by [[luck]]; [[fortunate]]; meeting with [[good]] [[success]] or good [[fortune]]; said of persons.
#:''a '''lucky''' adventurer''
#:''he is very '''lucky'''''
#Producing, or resulting in, good [[chance]], or unexpectedly; favorable; auspicious; fortunate.
#:''a '''lucky''' mistake''
#:''a '''lucky''' cast''
#:''a '''lucky''' hour''

====Synonyms====
*(''favored by luck''): [[fortunate]], [[successful]]
*(''producing or resulting in good chance''): [[auspicious]], [[favorable]], [[fortunate]]

